title: Hokusai The Great Wave Matted Notecard
description:
Print developed from Katsushika Hokusai’s The Great Wave, 1830-33, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

From the much-celebrated series Thirty-Six Views of Mount Fuji (Fugaku sanjurokkei)”, Hokusai’s woodblock print The Great Wave (1830/33), is one of the most famous and recognizable works of art in the world.

  • Print Reproduction
  • Image Dimensions: 6.375 x 4.343 in.
  • Full Dimensions: 8 x 10 in.
  • Materials: Premium cardstock
